<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>MediaLab Privacy Policy</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.png" type="image/png" />
  </head>
  <body class="min-h-screen bg-slate-950 text-slate-100">
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
      <a href="/" class="text-cyan-300 text-sm font-bold">Back to MediaLab</a>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-4xl font-black tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-slate-300 leading-7">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">What we collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">MediaLab may collect account details, project files you upload or publish, usage logs, payout details you submit for withdrawals, and connected-provider metadata from services like Google, GitHub, and Render.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">How we use data</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">We use your data to run the studio, publish projects, verify hosting, monitor platform health, process withdrawal requests, and improve product reliability and fraud protection.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Third-party services</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">MediaLab integrates with third-party providers such as Google, GitHub, and Render. Those services have their own policies and control parts of the data flow once you authorize them.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">Your control</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">You can disconnect integrations, delete hosted projects, and contact support for account issues. Sensitive provider tokens are handled server-side and are not intentionally exposed in client responses.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
